name: PKCS8EncodedKeySpec
comment:
This class represents the ASN.1 encoding of a private key, encoded according to the ASN.1 type {@code PrivateKeyInfo}. The {@code PrivateKeyInfo} syntax is defined in the PKCS#8 standard as follows: 
 PrivateKeyInfo ::= SEQUENCE {
   version Version,
   privateKeyAlgorithm PrivateKeyAlgorithmIdentifier,
   privateKey PrivateKey,
   attributes [0] IMPLICIT Attributes OPTIONAL }

 Version ::= INTEGER

 PrivateKeyAlgorithmIdentifier ::= AlgorithmIdentifier

 PrivateKey ::= OCTET STRING

 Attributes ::= SET OF Attribute

constructors.name: PKCS8EncodedKeySpec
constructors.comment: Creates a new PKCS8EncodedKeySpec with the given encoded key.

methods.name: getEncoded
methods.comment: Returns the key bytes, encoded according to the PKCS #8 standard.

methods.name: getFormat
methods.comment:
Returns the name of the encoding format associated with this
 key specification.
